<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1214">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7065.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s December 12 conveyed Obregon last night. He says was already
                            advised of Indian raids and had ordered General Estrada to move troops
                            from Guaymas for strengthening Yaqui River garrisons and that movement
                            is now under way; this will amply protect lives and property in Yaqui
                            Valley. Obregon leaving for south to-day.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>